<title>USA: Knoll gets FDA ok for hypertension drug.</title>
<headline>Knoll gets FDA ok for hypertension drug.</headline>
<dateline>MT. OLIVE, N.J. 1996-11-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Knoll Pharmaceutical Co said Friday that the Food and Drug Administration has cleared TARKA, Knoll's hypertension drug, for marketing.</p>
<p>Beginning in January TARKA should be available nationwide in four strengths, Knoll said.</p>
<p>The drug is indicated for treating hypertension as second line therapy for patients who need more than a single agent therapy, Knoll said.</p>
